														<p class="text-xs-16 mb-xs-4 color-black">Murray Kempton (1917–1997) was a columnist for <i>Newsday</i>, as well as a regular contributor to <i>The New York Review of Books</i>. His books include <i>Rebellions</i>, <i>Perversities, and Main Events</i>, and <i>The Briar Patch</i>, as well as <i>Part of Our Time</i>. He won the Pulitzer Prize in 1985.</p>
